# Core

- Keep changes **minimal and on-task**; do not refactor unrelated code or add scope the user did not request.
- **Match** existing naming, import style, and patterns in the files you touch.
- Prefer **conventional commands** for validation: [Makefile](Makefile) targets in [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) (`make format-all`, `make lint`, `make test`, `make fe-fmt`, `make fe-lint`, `make fe-test-ci`, `make lint-all`, `make test-all`). Run **one** `format-all`, **one** `lint-all`, and **one** `test-all` per substantive change batch ([validation policy](../AGENTS.md)). **Never** duct-tape lint with blanket ignores (`# noqa`, `eslint-disable`, etc.) just to turn checks green—fix the issue or narrowly justify suppressions aligned with repo patterns instead.
- **Do not** add unsolicited markdown docs; document in code only when the project already does so for similar code.
